                                <p class="text-justify"><b>Significance of Satsang:</b> In Sanskrit Satsang means “Sat = True”, “Sangam = company”. In Indian philosophy (1) the company of the "highest truth," (2) the company of a guru, or (3) company with an assembly of persons who listen to, talk about, and assimilate the truth. Satsangis a devotional speech and chanting programs for the upliftment of the Spirutual Knowledge & Divine Love consciousness of a devotee. This typically involves listening to or reading scriptures, reflecting on, discussing and assimilating their meaning, meditating on the source of these words, and bringing their meaning into one’s daily life.</p>
